---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About AdBunny — AI-Optimized Banner Monetization"
  description="AdBunny builds AI-optimized banner monetization technology so publishers can turn remnant inventory into revenue with minimal engineering effort."
  keywords="AdBunny ad monetization company, AI ad tech company, banner monetization technology"
>

<section class="min-h-[85vh] flex items-center" style="border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-border)">
  <div class="max-w-[80rem] mx-auto px-8 py-32 max-md:py-20 w-full">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-center max-md:grid-cols-1 max-md:gap-12">
      <div>
        <p class="kicker mb-8">About</p>
        <h1 class="font-serif leading-[1.08] tracking-tight mb-6" style="font-size:clamp(2.5rem,5vw,4rem);font-weight:550">we built AdBunny because remnant inventory deserved better tools</h1>
        <p class="text-base leading-relaxed mb-10 max-w-[28rem]" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">Remnant inventory monetization has historically meant static waterfalls, manual network ordering, and revenue left on the table. AdBunny replaces that with an AI optimization layer that does it continuously, automatically, per impression.</p>
        <a href="/get-started" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Get Your JS Tag</a>
      </div>
      <div>
        <img src="/images/about-hero-glow.png" alt="AdBunny premium ad monetization technology" class="w-full" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="py-32 max-md:py-20" style="border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-border)">
  <div class="max-w-[80rem] mx-auto px-8">
    <p class="kicker mb-12">What we believe</p>
    <h2 class="font-serif leading-[1.08] tracking-tight mb-16 max-md:mb-10" style="font-size:clamp(2rem,4vw,3rem);font-weight:550">our principles</h2>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-20 items-center max-md:grid-cols-1 max-md:gap-12">
      <div>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-10">
          <div style="border-top:1px solid var(--color-border);padding-top:1.5rem">
            <h3 class="font-serif text-xl tracking-tight mb-3" style="font-weight:550">integration should be simple</h3>
            <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">One JS tag should be enough. Never an engineering sprint.</p>
          </div>
          <div style="border-top:1px solid var(--color-border);padding-top:1.5rem">
            <h3 class="font-serif text-xl tracking-tight mb-3" style="font-weight:550">optimization should be real-time</h3>
            <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">Per impression, not on a quarterly review cycle.</p>
          </div>
          <div style="border-top:1px solid var(--color-border);padding-top:1.5rem">
            <h3 class="font-serif text-xl tracking-tight mb-3" style="font-weight:550">remnant shouldn't require trade-offs</h3>
            <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">It should just fill the gap. No choosing between your primary stack and new demand.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <img src="/images/about-principles-glow.png" alt="AdBunny core principles" class="w-full" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="py-32 max-md:py-20" style="border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-border)">
  <div class="max-w-[80rem] mx-auto px-8">
    <p class="kicker mb-12">Who we work with</p>
    <div class="max-w-[40rem]">
      <p class="text-base leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">Publishers and app developers monetizing remnant inventory, and ad networks, DSPs, and media buyers looking for efficient, programmatic access to that inventory.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="py-32 max-md:py-20 text-center">
  <div class="max-w-[80rem] mx-auto px-8">
    <h2 class="font-serif leading-[1.08] tracking-tight mb-6" style="font-size:clamp(2rem,4vw,3rem);font-weight:550">see AdBunny in action</h2>
    <a href="/get-started" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Get Your JS Tag</a>
  </div>
</section>
